changes.change_detail:
Technical modifications to ISO 10303- 203: 1994 are categorized as follows:This 
annex contains the documented changes from the previous version of ISO 10303 – 
203 (Amendment 1: 2000).  Many of the changes in this document are due to 
EXPRESS changes in 


  ISO 10303- 41: 2000 

  ISO 10303- 42: 2000 

  ISO 10303- 43: 2000 

  ISO 10303- 44: 2000 



Technical modifications to ISO 10303- 203: Amendment 1 (2000) are categorized as 
follows:


modifications to entities pre-fixed with cc_design

new EXPRESS declarations

EXPRESS declarations that were deleted


MODIFICATIONS TO ENTITIES PRE-FIXED WITH CC_DESIGN

In the following table the first column gives the Part 41 entities from which 
the column 2 and column 3 entities are subtypes.   The Amend.1 names are in 
column 2 and the Edition 2 names are in column 3. Details of the additional 
changes follow the table. Any changes in the column 1 entities are also noted.
  Part 41 Entity            203 Amend. 1 Subtype 203 Edition 2 Subtype


Part 41 entity203 Amend 1 subtype203 TS subtype

approval_assignmentcc_design_approvalapplied_approval_assignment

certification_assignmentcc_design_certificationapplied_certification_assignment

contract_assignmentcc_design_contractapplied_contract_assignment

date_and_time_assignmentcc_design_and_time_assignmentapplied_date_and_time_assignment

document_referencecc_design_specification_referenceapplied_document_reference

person_and_organizationcc_design_person_and_organization_assignmentapplied_person_and_organization_assignment

security_classification_assignmentcc_design_security_classificationapplied_security_classification_assignment



Rows 1- 2:  entity names only changed from Column 2 to Column 3.

Row 3 – 7: entity names and additional changes are noted below followed by the 
Express.

Row 3 Changes:  contracted_item replaced by contract_item with action added to 
SELECT list.


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

ENTITY cc_design_contract
  SUBTYPE OF (contract_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF contracted_item;
END_ENTITY; -- cc_design_contract

TYPE contracted_item = SELECT
  (product_definition_formation);
END_TYPE; -- contracted_item

Edition 2 Express

 ENTITY applied_contract_assignment
  SUBTYPE OF (contract_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF contract_item;
END_ENTITY; -- applied_contract_assignment

TYPE contract_item = SELECT
   (action, product_definition_formation);
END_TYPE; -- contract_item

Row 4 Changes:  WHERE rule dropped from 203 Amend. 1 to 203 Edition 2.


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

 ENTITY cc_design_date_and_time_assignment
  SUBTYPE OF (date_and_time_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF date_time_item;
WHERE
  WR1: cc_design_date_time_correlation(SELF);
END_ENTITY; -- cc_design_date_and_time_assignment

Edition 2 Express

ENTITY applied_date_and_time_assignment
  SUBTYPE OF (date_and_time_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF date_time_item;
END_ENTITY; -- applied_date_and_time_assignment

Row 5 Changes:  specified_item replaced by document_reference_item with 
action_method, product_definition_relationship, 
shape_aspect_relationship, versioned_action_request,   product,    
product_definition, and product_definition_formation added to 
document_reference_item SELECT list.


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

ENTITY cc_design_specification_reference
  SUBTYPE OF (document_reference);
  items : SET [1:?] OF specified_item;
END_ENTITY; -- cc_design_specification_reference

TYPE specified_item = SELECT
  (product_definition,
   shape_aspect);
END_TYPE; -- specified_item

Edition 2 Express

ENTITY applied_document_reference
SUBTYPE OF (document_reference);
  items : SET [1 : ?] OF document_reference_item;
END_ENTITY;
TYPE document_reference_item = SELECT (
   action_method,
   product_definition_relationship,
   shape_aspect,
   shape_aspect_relationship,
   versioned_action_request,
   product,
   product_definition,
   product_definition_formation);
END_TYPE; -- document_reference_item


Row 6 Changes:  person_organization_item replaced by 
person_and_organization_item with several changes to SELECT lists that are 
discussed under Related Changes.


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

ENTITY cc_design_person_and_organization_assignment
  SUBTYPE OF (person_and_organization_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF person_organization_item;
WHERE
  WR1: cc_design_person_and_organization_correlation(SELF);
END_ENTITY; -- cc_design_person_and_organization_assignment

TYPE person_organization_item = SELECT
  (change,
   start_work,
   change_request,
   start_request,
   configuration_item,
   product,
   product_definition_formation,
   product_definition,
   contract,
   security_classification);
END_TYPE; -- person_organization_item

Edition 2 Express

ENTITY applied_person_and_organization_assignment
  SUBTYPE OF (person_and_organization_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF person_and_organization_item;
END_ENTITY;

TYPE person_and_organization_item = SELECT (
   action,
   alternate_product_relationship,
   applied_action_assignment,
   applied_identification_assignment,
   applied_security_classification_assignment,
   approval,
   assembly_component_usage_substitute,
   certification,
   configuration_item,
   contract,
   document_file,
   executed_action,
   general_property,
   organizational_project,
   product,
   product_definition,
   product_definition_formation
   product_definition_formation_relationship,
   property_definition,
   security_classification,
   shape_representation,
   versioned_action_request,
   );
END_TYPE;

Related Changes
A.  change and start_work
The action_assignment supertype (Part 41entity) had a derived attribute 
and a where rule added.  The entities change and start_work were replaced by 
applied_action_assignment with action_items having additional entities in the 
SELECT list.


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

ENTITY action_assignment
  ABSTRACT SUPERTYPE;
  assigned_action : action;
END_ENTITY; -- action_assignment

ENTITY change
  SUBTYPE OF (action_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF work_item;
END_ENTITY; -- change

ENTITY start_work
  SUBTYPE OF (action_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF work_item;
END_ENTITY; -- start_work

TYPE work_item = SELECT
  (product_definition_formation);
END_TYPE; -- work_item


203 Edition 2 Express

ENTITY action_assignment
  ABSTRACT SUPERTYPE;
  assigned_action : action;
DERIVE
  role : object_role := get_role (SELF);
WHERE
  WR1: SIZEOF (USEDIN (SELF, 'CONFIGURATION_CONTROL_3D_DESIGN_ED2_MIM.' + 
'ROLE_ASSOCIATION.ITEM_WITH_ROLE')) >= 1;
END_ENTITY;

ENTITY applied_action_assignment
SUBTYPE OF (action_assignment);
  items : SET [1 : ?] OF action_items;
END_ENTITY;

TYPE action_items = SELECT (
   configuration_effectivity,
   product_definition,
   product_definition_formation,
   product_definition_formation_relationship,
   product_definition_relationship);
END_TYPE;

B.  change_request and start_request
Note that the supertype action_request_assignment (Part 41 entity) was modified 
by adding a derived attribute and a where rule.  The subtype entities 
change_request and start_request  have been replaced by 
applied_action_assignment with action_request_item having additional entities in 
the SELECT list.


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

ENTITY action_request_assignment
  ABSTRACT SUPERTYPE;
  assigned_action_request : versioned_action_request;
END_ENTITY; -- action_request_assignment

ENTITY change_request
  SUBTYPE OF (action_request_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF change_request_item;
END_ENTITY; -- change_request

TYPE change_request_item = SELECT
  (product_definition_formation);
END_TYPE; -- change_request_item

ENTITY start_request
  SUBTYPE OF (action_request_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF start_request_item;
END_ENTITY; -- start_request

TYPE start_request_item = SELECT
  (product_definition_formation);
END_TYPE; -- start_request_item

203 Edition 2 Express
ENTITY action_request_assignment
  ABSTRACT SUPERTYPE;
  assigned_action_request : versioned_action_request;
DERIVE
  role : object_role := get_role (SELF);
WHERE
  WR1: SIZEOF (USEDIN (SELF, 'CONFIGURATION_CONTROL_3D_DESIGN_ED2_MIM.' + 
'ROLE_ASSOCIATION.ITEM_WITH_ROLE')) >= 1;
END_ENTITY;

ENTITY applied_action_request_assignment
SUBTYPE OF (action_request_assignment);
  items : SET [1 : ?] OF action_request_item;
END_ENTITY;

TYPE action_request_item = SELECT (
   product_definition,
   product_definition_formation,
   product_definition_formation_relationship,
   product_definition_relationship,
   property_definition);
END_TYPE;


Row 7 Changes:  security_classification_assignment supertype (Part 41) has a new 
derived attribute and a where rule.  The security_classification_item has some 
additional entities in the SELECT list.


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

ENTITY security_classification_assignment
 ABSTRACT SUPERTYPE;
  assigned_security_classification: security_classification;
END_ENTITY; -- security_classification_assignment
ENTITY cc_design_security_classification
  SUBTYPE OF (security_classification_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF classified_item;
END_ENTITY; -- cc_design_security_classification
TYPE classified_item = SELECT
  (product_definition_formation,
   assembly_component_usage);
END_TYPE; -- classified_item
Edition 2 Express

ENTITY security_classification_assignment
  ABSTRACT SUPERTYPE;
  assigned_security_classification : security_classification;
DERIVE
  role : object_role := get_role (SELF);
WHERE
  WR1: SIZEOF(USEDIN(SELF, 'CONFIGURATION_CONTROL_3D_DESIGN_ED2_MIM.' + 
'ROLE_ASSOCIATION.ITEM_WITH_ROLE')) >= 1;
END_ENTITY;

ENTITY applied_security_classification_assignment
  SUBTYPE OF (security_classification_assignment);
  items : SET [1:?] OF security_classification_item;
END_ENTITY;

TYPE security_classification_item = SELECT (
   assembly_component_usage,
   product_definition_usage,
   document_file,
   product,
   product_definition,
   product_definition_formation);
END_TYPE;

MODIFIED EXPRESS DECLARATIONS
The following EXPRESS type declarations were modified from Amend. 1 (2000) to 
203 Edition 2:

ahead_or_behind


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

TYPE ahead_or_behind = ENUMERATION OF
  (ahead,
   behind);
END_TYPE; -- ahead_or_behind

Edition 2 Express

TYPE ahead_or_behind = ENUMERATION OF 
  (ahead, exact, behind);
END_TYPE;

characterized_definition


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

TYPE characterized_definition = SELECT
  (characterized_product_definition,
   shape_definition);
END_TYPE; -- characterized_definition

Edition 2 Express

TYPE characterized_definition = SELECT 
  (characterized_object, characterized_product_definition, shape_definition);
END_TYPE;


second_in_minute

Amendment 1 EXPRESS

TYPE second_in_minute = REAL;
WHERE
  WR1: (0 >= SELF) AND (SELF > 60);
END_TYPE; -- second_in_minute

Edition 2 Express

TYPE second_in_minute = REAL;
WHERE
  wr1 : {0 >= SELF <= 60.0};
END_TYPE;

unit

Amendment 1 EXPRESS

TYPE unit = SELECT
  (named_unit);
END_TYPE; -- unit

Edition 2 Express

TYPE unit = SELECT 
  (derived_unit, named_unit);
END_TYPE;

The following EXPRESS entity declarations were modified from Amend. 1 (2000) to 
203 Edition 2:
action


Amendment 1 EXPRESS

ENTITY action;
  name          : label;
  description   : text;
  chosen_method : action_method;
END_ENTITY; -- action

Edition 2 Express

ENTITY action;
  name : label;
  description : OPTIONAL text;
  chosen_method : action_method;
DERIVE
  id : identifier := get_id_value(SELF);
WHERE
  wr1 : SIZEOF(USEDIN(SELF, 
    'CONFIGURATION_CONTROL_3D_DESIGN_ED2_MIM_LF.ID_ATTRIBUTE.IDENTIFIED_ITEM'))
     >= 1;
END_ENTITY;

